@{
    ViewBag.Title = $"Privacy notice on {Constants.SERVICE_NAME}";
}

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">
            ‘Check if you are eligible for an energy grant for a home with no gas boiler (Home Upgrade Grant)’ Portal Privacy Notice
        </h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            This notice is provided by the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero and sets out how we will use your personal data, and
            your rights. It is made under Articles 13 and/or 14 of the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR). 
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            This portal is for authorised users to download data about citizens that believe that they may be eligible for a HUG2 grant.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            This privacy notice only relates to how the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ) uses your data in connection with
            the portal. 
        </p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Your data
        </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            The HUG 2 Eligibility Checker portal uses your email address to identify your user account, and also records:
        </p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li class="govuk-body">The local authority areas you can access</li>
            <li class="govuk-body">The date and time that you download a file of citizens' data</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Purpose
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            We will process your personal data for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li class="govuk-body">To allow you to use the portal and to see the correct files to download.</li>
            <li class="govuk-body">To audit the downloading of citizens' data.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Legal basis of processing
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            The legal basis for processing your data is that processing is necessary for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest.
            Specifically, the task is the delivery of the low carbon and energy efficiency objectives of the HUG2 grant scheme, in accordance with
            the Warm Homes and Energy Conservation Act 2000 and the Climate Change Act 2008.
        </p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Recipients
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            We may share your personal data with our contractors and data processors for the purpose of delivering, monitoring, evaluating or improving
            the service. As your personal data will be stored on our IT infrastructure it will also be shared with our data processors Amazon AWS and GOV.UK Notify. 
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            We will share your data with other public bodies if we are required to do so by law - for example, by court order, or to prevent fraud or other crime. 
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">
            Retention
        </h3>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Your data will be kept by us for no more than two years after the funding period for HUG 2 has ended. 
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Your rights
        </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to request information about how your personal data are processed, and to request a copy of that personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to request that any inaccuracies in your personal data are rectified without delay.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to request that any incomplete personal data are completed, including by means of a supplementary statement.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to request that your personal data are erased if there is no longer a justification for them to be processed.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right in certain circumstances (for example, where accuracy is contested) to request that the processing of your personal data is restricted.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data where it is processed for direct marketing purposes.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            To exercise your rights, contact the Data Protection Officer using the contact details below.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            International transfers
        </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            As your personal data is stored on our IT infrastructure and shared with our data processors Amazon AWS and GOV.UK Notify, it may be 
            transferred and stored securely in the UK and European Economic Area.  Where your personal data is stored outside the UK and EEA it
            will be subject to equivalent legal protection through the use of Model Contract Clauses.
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Complaints
        </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            If you consider that your personal data has been misused or mishandled, you may make a complaint to the Information Commissioner, who is an independent regulator. 
        </p>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            The Information Commissioner can be contacted at:
        </p>
        <div class="govuk-inset-text">
            <p class="govuk-body">
                Information Commissioner's Office<br>
                Wycliffe House<br>
                Water Lane<br>
                Wilmslow<br>
                Cheshire<br>
                SK9 5AF<br>
            </p>
            <ul class="govuk-list">
                <li>Telephone: 0303 123 1113</li>
                <li>Monday to Friday, 9am to 5pm (except public holidays)</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="govuk-body">
                <a class="govuk-link" href="https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/" target="_blank">https://ico.org.uk/make-a-complaint/</a>
            </p>
        </div>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            Any complaint to the Information Commissioner is without prejudice to your right to seek redress through the courts.  
        </p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
            Contact Details
        </h2>
        <p class="govuk-body">
            The data controller for your personal data is the Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (DESNZ).
        </p>
